{
  "page": "Double wedding at Casterly Rock",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>double wedding at Casterly Rock</b> occurred in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_235_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">235&#160;AC</a> where <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Lord of Casterly Rock\">Lord of Casterly Rock</a>, married his two eldest surviving sons, <a href=\"/index.php/Tion_Lannister\" title=\"Tion Lannister\">Tion</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a>, to Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn Reyne</a> and Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Marbrand\" title=\"Jeyne Marbrand\">Jeyne Marbrand</a> respectively.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Backgrounds\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Backgrounds</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Weddings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Weddings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Backgrounds\">Backgrounds</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Double_wedding_at_Casterly_Rock&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Backgrounds\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c9/Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg/300px-Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"268\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c9/Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg/450px-Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c9/Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg/600px-Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellyn_Reyne_and_Jeyne_Marbrand_by_Magali_Villeneuve.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The brides Ellyn Reyne and Jeyne Marbrand, by Magali Villeneuve for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a> had four sons with his second wife, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">Rohanne Webber</a>; the eldests were a set of twins, <a href=\"/index.php/Tywald_Lannister\" title=\"Tywald Lannister\">Tywald</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tion_Lannister\" title=\"Tion Lannister\">Tion</a> (b. 210's AC), followed by <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_220_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">220&#160;AC</a>) and then <a href=\"/index.php/Jason_Lannister_(son_of_Gerold)\" title=\"Jason Lannister (son of Gerold)\">Jason</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_229_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">229&#160;AC</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Several years prior to the <a href=\"/index.php/Peake_Uprising\" title=\"Peake Uprising\">Peake Uprising</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/233_AC\" title=\"233 AC\">233&#160;AC</a>, Tywald was betrothed to <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn Reyne</a>, the daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Reyne\" title=\"Robert Reyne\">Robert Reyne</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Castamere\" title=\"Lord of Castamere\">Lord of Castamere</a>. When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">Peake</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Starpike\" title=\"Starpike\">Starpike</a> rose in rebellion against King <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar I Targaryen</a> a host of <a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">westermen</a> aided Maekar to put down the rebellion. Tywald served as Lord Robert's squire during the conflict but both died during the <a href=\"/index.php/Storming_of_Starpike\" title=\"Storming of Starpike\">storming of Starpike</a>, as well as King Maekar. Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighted</a> Tywald as he laid dying in Tion's arms. Later that year, Lord Gerold made the journey to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to the assembled <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Council\" title=\"Great Council\">Great Council</a> to elect Maekar's successor to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. Gerold's eloquence (and some say <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>) helped Prince Aegon to win the election. Born the fourth son of a fourth son, Aegon became known as \"Aegon the Unlikely\" from that day forth, and he ruled as Aegon V Targaryen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Grieving the death of his heir and the disappearance of his wife three years earlier, Lord Gerold became ill and a pale shadow of the man once dubbed \"Gerold the Golden\". Not abandoning her ambition to become Lady of Casterly Rock someday, Lady Ellyn took advantage of Gerold's apparent weakness to convince Tion to marry her in place of his late twin. Lord Gerold opposed the match at first but then agreed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Weddings\">Weddings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Double_wedding_at_Casterly_Rock&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Weddings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A double ceremony was held at Casterly Rock in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_235_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">235&#160;AC</a> to marry Tion and Ellyn as well as the fifteen-year-old Tytos to <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Marbrand\" title=\"Jeyne Marbrand\">Jeyne Marbrand</a>, the daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Marbrand\" title=\"Alyn Marbrand\">Alyn Marbrand</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Ashemark\" title=\"Lord of Ashemark\">Lord of Ashemark</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Double_wedding_at_Casterly_Rock&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Following the weddings, Gerold retreated into his books and bedchamber, leaving Tion and Ellyn to rule as Lord and Lady of Casterly Rock in all but name. Ellyn hosted splendid <a href=\"/index.php/Tournament\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tournament\">tournaments</a> and balls, and used her new position to empower her own <a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\">house</a>. Ellyn's power over the Rock did not last long, however. After the death of Ser Tion at the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_Wendwater_Bridge\" title=\"Battle of Wendwater Bridge\">Battle of Wendwater Bridge</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/236_AC\" title=\"236 AC\">236&#160;AC</a>, Lord Gerold took a firm hold of the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> once more. He became intent on preparing Tytos for lordship.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In accordance with the <a href=\"/index.php/Widow%27s_Law\" title=\"Widow&#39;s Law\">Widow's Law</a>, Lady Ellyn was allowed to stay at the Rock but her power at court diminished greatly. The favors and gifts Ellyn once received were now bestowed upon her goodsister, Lady Jeyne. A fierce rivalry, dubbed the \"<a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Wombs\" title=\"War of the Wombs\">War of the Wombs</a>\" by Gerold's <a href=\"/index.php/Fool\" title=\"Fool\">fool</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Toad\" title=\"Lord Toad\">Lord Toad</a>, began between the two ladies. In a last ditch effort to regain power, Lady Ellyn seduced Tytos in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_239_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">239&#160;AC</a> and tried to convince him to set aside Jeyne for her. Intimidated, Tytos was not able to perform and confessed the affair to his wife, who in turn informed Lord Gerold. Furious, Gerold married off Ellyn to <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a>, the aged Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a>, and she never returned to Casterly Rock.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lady Jeyne forgave Tytos for the incident and they had five children in the following years; <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_242_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">242&#160;AC</a>), <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_244_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">244&#160;AC</a>), <a href=\"/index.php/Genna_Lannister\" title=\"Genna Lannister\">Genna</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_245_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">245&#160;AC</a>), <a href=\"/index.php/Tygett_Lannister\" title=\"Tygett Lannister\">Tygett</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_250_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">250&#160;AC</a>) and <a href=\"/index.php/Gerion_Lannister\" title=\"Gerion Lannister\">Gerion</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_255_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">255&#160;AC</a>). Tytos succeeded his father after his death of a bad bladder in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_244_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">244&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Double_wedding_at_Casterly_Rock&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Westerlands: House Lanniste